== Description ==
'''Phenomenon 31''', also called "'''Reformation'''" or (most commonly) "'''Rewrite'''", is a process that multiple levels in [[The Database]] go through upon being discovered by the [[M.E.G.]] Said process usually involves the addition of different properties, items, Person of Interests, entities, and more; while Reformations can happen to about any level stored within the Backrooms, the phenomenon itself seems to only take place in levels with little information to it (excluding [[Level 0]]). 

According to many researchers, Reformation typically occurs if a level has the following:

*A dull or plain background with little notable events,
*Insufficient information enough for the M.E.G. to write so easily about,
*An increasingly high but unexplained danger level,
*A low, boring location without any threats,
*Or a messy, almost out-of-tone level to the nature of the Backrooms itself.

== Speculation ==
Due to how little the M.E.G. and various other groups have gathered concerning Phenomenon 31, there have been many papers submitted pertaining to its existence and nature; the following are the most popular theories regarding the Rewriting process, as shown down below.

<div class="styled-quote"><span class="titlebox">THE MODERATOR THEORY</span>
''The most straightforward and widely accepted theory—''

Given that Phenomenon 31 tends to happen only to levels that seem "out of place" in the Backrooms, this has led many people into believing that there may be something or someone controlling how the level design works. This is further backed up by the fact that Phenomenon 31 occurs only when the M.E.G. has decided to add it into The Database, implying some sort of force connected to it.

This isn't the first time The Database has been shown to be related to higher dimensional beings either, as some entities like [[The Narrator]] have consistently shown to be able to manipulate the context and backgrounds of various levels; leaving this to be the most famous and well-regarded theory pertaining to Phenomenon 31's nature.

</div>


<div class="styled-quote"><span class="titlebox">THE METAMORPHOSIS THEORY</span>
''The second most popular theory accepted by skeptics—''

While this takes inspiration from the Moderator Theory, the Metamorphosis Theory proposes an entirely different outlook on Phenomenon 31. Instead of a supernatural force "editing" the level, the level is editing ''itself.'' 

Assuming that Phenomenon 31 only occurs once the M.E.G. finds out about a level's existence, many critics of the Moderator Theory has suggested that if the being editing the levels were truly "omniscient" or "omnipotent," they wouldn't need to continue remaking the levels as they deem fit.

However, this theory has been debunked multiple times, and newer evidence that have recently been found certainly disprove of this proposal.

</div>

== History ==
The first sighting of Phenomenon 31 took place on '''April 13th''', '''2010''', where it was reported by Dr. Mike Alder to leading researcher Brent Stiles in the following phone call. It should be noted that while the discovery took place on the aforementioned date, the Reformation processes have likely been around for much, much longer.

<div class="titleblock" style="padding-top: 2px; padding-bottom: 2px;">
<br>
'''[CALL BEGINS]'''

'''Stiles''': Yes?

'''Alder''': Hey. It's me again.

'''Stiles''': (''Pauses'') Jane's boyfriend?

'''Alder''': You don't need to call me that, but yes.

'''Stiles''': Ah, right. Yeah, what do you need, Mike?

'''Alder''': Nothing, really. You- you haven't heard the news about the new level? You know, the one you helped write. The team just updated its page.

'''Stiles''': I don't exactly ''edit'' the pages, I just gather information for them. Is there anything you need? I know you wouldn't be calling if there wasn't an emergency.

'''Alder''': No, it's not an emergency. More like a breakthrough. I'm calling you right now because I want you to report something to the leading directors. Via email, phone call, whatever. Just report it—

'''Stiles''': (''Interrupting'') What happened?

'''Alder''': You haven't looked at the new page?

'''Stiles''': No, what happened?

'''Alder''': Look on there first. I can't exactly explain it right now.

(''Sound of typing.'')

'''Stiles''': Let's see, where— ah. Alright, I'm clicking on it now. Should be labelled a stub article right? (''Pauses, seemingly scrolling down'') One second.

(''Mouse clicks.'')

'''Stiles''': Holy—

'''Alder''': ''Yeah.'' A bunch of new stuff just came in.

'''Stiles''': What? What- what even ''is'' this? The level was supposed to be a barren desert, how'd it turn out to be a surreal wild west movie set with Clint Eastwood? Hold on, when did this happen?

'''Alder''': Just now.

'''Stiles''': ''Just now?'' Like, recently?

'''Alder''': Yeah. I don't know how it happened. A bunch of props just spawned in. We called in a recovery team; they're doing everything they can to diagnose the events that just occurred. We're thinking it could be a different phenomenon entirely. (''Chuckles'') Like I said, breakthrough.

'''Stiles''': Alright. Alright, well, thanks for telling me. I'll send an email or something. Make sure you take good notes.

'''Alder''': Yeah, I will. OH SH—

(''Phone cuts off for a moment.'')

'''Stiles''': Michael? Hello?

(''Silence for 3 seconds.'')

'''Stiles''': Michael? Are you there? Hello? Michael, ''are you alright?!''

'''Alder''': (''Panting'') Yeah. Yeah, I'm fine. Jesus.

'''Stiles''': What happened?

'''Alder''': A hay barrel just fell straight from the sky.

'''Stiles''': What?

'''Alder''': No, like, it just manifested or something and then began falling down. Look! Look, there's another!

(''Indistinct chatter.'')

'''Stiles''': Hello?

'''Alder''': (''Away from mic'') Yeah, get the camera. Try getting a picture. 

'''Stiles''': Mike?

'''Alder''': Yeah, sorry. I-I think I'll need to move. Not safe to be here. Nearly just died.

'''Stiles''': Of course. Get back to me when you can. Stay safe.

'''Alder''': You too. Bye.

'''Stiles''': Bye. Talk later.

'''[CALL ENDS]'''

</div>






























